{"title_page": "Geronimo Allison", "text_new": "{{short description|American football wide receiver}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=January 2020}}\n{{Infobox NFL biography\n| name          = Geronimo Allison\n| image         = \n| image_size    = \n| alt           = \n| caption       = \n| current_team  = Detroit Lions\n| number        = \n| position      = [[Wide receiver]]\n| birth_date    = {{birth date and age|1994|1|18}}\n| birth_place   = [[Tampa, Florida]]\n| height_ft     = 6\n| height_in     = 3\n| weight_lbs    = 202\n| high_school   = [[Spoto High School|Spoto]] ([[Riverview, Florida]])\n| college       = [[Illinois Fighting Illini football|Illinois]]\n| undraftedyear = 2016\n| pastteams     =\n* [[Green Bay Packers]] ({{NFL Year|2016}}\u2013{{NFL Year|2019}})\n* [[Detroit Lions]] ({{NFL Year|2020}}\u2013present)\n| status        = Active\n| statweek      = \n| statseason    = 2019\n| statlabel1    = [[Reception (gridiron football)|Receptions]]\n| statvalue1    = 89\n| statlabel2    = Receiving yards\n| statvalue2    = 1,045\n| statlabel3    = [[Touchdown|Receiving touchdowns]]\n| statvalue3    = 6\n| nflnew        = geronimoallison/2556460\n}}\n'''Geronimo John Allison''' (born January 18, 1994) is an [[American football]] [[wide receiver]] for the [[Detroit Lions]] of the [[National Football League]] (NFL). He played [[college football]] at [[Illinois Fighting Illini football|Illinois]], and was signed by the Packers as an [[undrafted free agent]] in 2016.\n\n==Early life==\nIn an interview with ''[[The News-Gazette (Champaign-Urbana)|The News-Gazette]]'', Allison said his mother Melissa Glover gave him his first name because she wanted to give him \"a unique name.\"<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.news-gazette.com/sports/illini-sports/football/2014-10-10/qa-geronimo-allison.html |title=Q&A with Geronimo Allison |last=Asmussen |first=Bob  |date=October 10, 2014 |newspaper=The News-Gazette |access-date=January 16, 2017}}</ref> He credits his mother with instilling his religious faith, which he expresses in post-game prayers with opponents and teammates at midfield.<ref name=\"MilJS\">{{cite web |last1=Hendricks |first1=Martin |title=Allison thankful for opportunity |url=https://www.jsonline.com/story/sports/nfl/packers/2016/11/16/player-profile-allison-thankful-opportunity/93992946/ |website=Milwaukee Journal Sentinel |accessdate=October 4, 2018 }}</ref>\n\nAllison attended [[Spoto High School]] in [[Riverview, Florida]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.espn.com/blog/green-bay-packers/post/_/id/31726/nearly-a-never-was-rookie-receiver-geronimo-allison-catches-packers-eye |title=Nearly a 'never was,' rookie receiver Geronimo Allison catches Packers' eye |last=Wilde |first=Jason |date=August 4, 2016 |publisher=ESPN |access-date=January 16, 2017}}</ref> He was academically ineligible his sophomore and junior years, but worked in private classes with the coach's wife Anne Caparaso to improve his grades and had a successful senior season.<ref name=MilJS />\n\n==College career==\nDue to his academic struggles in high school, Allison began college at [[Iowa Western Community College]] in [[Council Bluffs, Iowa]]. He proved a bright student, finishing an associate degree in just three semesters; he also led the team to a 22\u20131 record in two seasons, an NJCAA title, and led the conference in receptions, yards, and touchdowns his second year.<ref name=MilJS />\n\nAllison transferred to the [[University of Illinois at Urbana\u2013Champaign|University of Illinois]], where he played for the [[Illinois Fighting Illini football|Fighting Illini]] in 2014 and 2015.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://fightingillini.com/roster.aspx?rp_id=2171|title=Illinois Fighting Illini: Geronimo Allison|work=FightingIllini.com|accessdate=October 14, 2016}}</ref> His junior year, he was usually the second option to freshman star [[Mike Dudek]], though he caught five touchdowns to Dudek's six for the 6\u20137 Illini. In week 3, he had a career-high six receptions for 160 yards and two touchdowns in a lopsided loss to [[2014 Washington Huskies football team|Washington]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Illinois at Washington Box Score, September 13, 2014 |url=https://www.sports-reference.com/cfb/boxscores/2014-09-13-washington.html |website=College Football at Sports-Reference.com }}</ref> Allison took over the top spot his senior year, replacing the injured Dudek for 882 yards but only three touchdowns during the [[2015 Illinois Fighting Illini football team|5\u20137 campaign]]. He had over 90 yards receiving in five of the first seven games, but five or fewer receptions in the final five games of the season.<ref name=\"colglog\">{{cite web |title=Geronimo Allison Career Game Log |url=https://www.sports-reference.com/cfb/players/geronimo-allison-1/gamelog/ |website=College Football at Sports-Reference.com }}</ref> He was an All-Big Ten honorable mention, and won the team's Service Above Self award.<ref name=MilJS />\n\n===College statistics===\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align: center;\"\n|-\n! colspan=\"8\" style=\"{{CollegePrimaryStyle|Illinois Fighting Illini|color=white}};\" |'''Illinois Fighting Illini'''\n|-\n! rowspan=\"2\"|Year !! colspan=\"2\"|Games !! colspan=\"5\"|Receiving\n|-\n! G !! GS !! Rec !! Yds !! Avg !! Lng !! TD\n|-\n! [[2014 Illinois Fighting Illini football team|2014]]\n| 13 || 12 || 41 || 598 || 14.6 || 60 || 5\n|-\n! [[2015 Illinois Fighting Illini football team|2015]]\n| 12 || 11 || 65 || 882 || 13.6 || 53 || 3\n|-\n! Total || 24 || 22 || 106 || 1,480 || 14.0 || 60 || 8\n|-\n| colspan=\"8\"|<small>Source: [http://fightingillini.com/roster.aspx?rp_id=2171 FightingIllini.com]</small>\n|}\n\n==Professional career==\n{{external media\n| video1 = [http://www.nfl.com/videos/nfl-combine/0ap3000000643704/2016-combine-workout-geronimo-allison Allison's NFL Combine workout]\n}}\n{{nfl predraft\n|    height ft = 6\n|    height in = {{fraction|3|1|4}}\n|       weight = 196\n|         dash = 4.67\n|    ten split = 1.65\n| twenty split = 2.74\n|      shuttle = 4.28\n|   cone drill = 7.40\n|     vertical = 33\n|     broad ft = 10\n|     broad in = 7\n|    wonderlic = 13<ref>{{cite web|url=http://archive.jsonline.com/sports/packers/rookie-free-agents-for-the-green-bay-packers-b99719308z1-378205081.html|title=A closer look at the Packers rookie free agents|last=McGinn|first=Bob|work=JSOnline.com|date=May 6, 2016|accessdate=April 21, 2018|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180421164405/http://archive.jsonline.com/sports/packers/rookie-free-agents-for-the-green-bay-packers-b99719308z1-378205081.html|archivedate=April 21, 2018}}</ref>\n|     arm span = {{fraction|32|7|8}}\n|    hand span = {{fraction|9|1|2}}\n|         note = All values are from [[NFL Scouting Combine|NFL Combine]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nfl.com/combine/profiles/geronimo-allison?id=2555211|title=NFL Events: Combine Player Profiles \u2013 Geronimo Allison|publisher=National Football League|accessdate=July 30, 2016|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180418030707/http://www.nfl.com/combine/profiles/geronimo-allison?id=2555211|archivedate=April 18, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://draftscout.com/ratings/dsprofile.php?pyid=132233&draftyear=2016&genpos=|title=Geronimo Allison \u2013 Illinois, WR : 2016 NFL Draft Scout Player Profile|work=DraftScout.com|accessdate=July 30, 2016|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180418030929/http://draftscout.com/ratings/dsprofile.php?pyid=132233&draftyear=2016&genpos=|archivedate=April 18, 2018}}</ref>\n}}\n\n===2016 season: Rookie year===\nAfter going undrafted in the [[2016 NFL Draft]], Allison signed with the [[Green Bay Packers]] on May 6, 2016.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.packers.com/news-and-events/article-press-release/article-1/packers-sign-19-rookie-free-agents/b9554146-c6a7-4362-b196-3878cbfe8295 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170821212438/http://www.packers.com/news-and-events/article-press-release/article-1/packers-sign-19-rookie-free-agents/b9554146-c6a7-4362-b196-3878cbfe8295 |archive-date=August 21, 2017 |title=Packers sign 19 rookie free agents |date=May 6, 2016 |website=Packers.com |url-status=dead |access-date=July 30, 2016}}</ref>\n\nOn September 3, 2016, Allison was released by the Packers during final team cuts,<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.packers.com/news-and-events/article-roster-moves/article-1/packers-keep-six-undrafted-rookies-including-qb-joe-callahan/9e6d9856-8feb-4a8d-b038-90cfcff1b0b3 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180402184923/http://www.packers.com/news-and-events/article-roster-moves/article-1/packers-keep-six-undrafted-rookies-including-qb-joe-callahan/9e6d9856-8feb-4a8d-b038-90cfcff1b0b3 |url-status=dead |archive-date=April 2, 2018 |title=Packers keep six undrafted rookies, including QB Joe Callahan |date=September 3, 2016 |website=Packers.com |access-date=September 3, 2016}}</ref> but re-signed to the Packers' [[practice squad]] two days later.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.packers.com/news/packers-sign-ls-goode-claim-rb-pressley-17624159 |title=Packers sign LS Goode; claim RB Pressley |date=September 5, 2016 |website=Packers.com |access-date=October 4, 2016}}</ref> On October 24, 2016, he was promoted from the practice squad to the active roster.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.packers.com/news/packers-promote-wr-allison-s-whitehead-to-active-roster-17952592 |title=Packers promote WR Allison, S Whitehead to active roster |date=October 24, 2016 |website=Packers.com |url-status=dead |access-date=October 24, 2016 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190218081841/https://www.packers.com/news/packers-promote-wr-allison-s-whitehead-to-active-roster-17952592 |archive-date=February 18, 2019 }}</ref> Allison made his NFL debut against the [[2016 Atlanta Falcons season|Atlanta Falcons]] in Week 8. His first career NFL reception came as a four-yard touchdown from [[Aaron Rodgers]] in the second quarter.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.espn.com/blog/green-bay-packers/post/_/id/34647/encouraging-sign-aaron-rodgers-and-packers-offense-back-on-track|title=Encouraging sign: Aaron Rodgers, Packers' offense back on track|last=Demovsky|first=Rob|publisher=ESPN|date=October 31, 2016|accessdate=October 31, 2016}}</ref> \n\nAllison finished his rookie year with 12 receptions for 202 yards and two touchdowns in ten games and two starts.\n\n===2017 season===\nOn July 19, 2017, Allison was suspended for the first game of the 2017 season for violating the league's substance-abuse policy.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://profootballtalk.nbcsports.com/2017/07/19/geronimo-allison-suspended-for-first-game-of-regular-season/ |title=Geronimo Allison suspended for first game of regular season |last=Florio |first=Mike |date=July 19, 2017 |website=ProFootballTalk.NBCSports.com}}</ref> During Week 3, he had career-highs with six receptions and 122 yards against the [[2018 Cincinnati Bengals season|Cincinnati Bengals]], and finished fourth among Packers receivers on the season with 23 receptions.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.cbssports.com/fantasy/football/news/packers-geronimo-allison-drops-122-yards-on-bengals/ |title=Packers' Geronimo Allison: Drops 122 yards on Bengals |work=CBSSports.com |access-date=October 9, 2018 }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.pro-football-reference.com/teams/gnb/2017.htm |title=2017 Green Bay Packers Statistics & Players |website=Pro-Football-Reference.com  |access-date=October 9, 2018}}</ref>\n\nAllison finished his second professional season with 23 receptions for 253 yards.\n\n===2018 season===\nAllison was re-signed by the Packers on March 14, 2018.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.packers.com/news-and-events/article-daily-news-story/article-1/negotiating-window-opens-today-for-pending-nfl-free-agents/d8742ef7-d15c-43be-9959-72d670a9f2b1|title=Negotiating window opens today for pending NFL free agents|last=Hodkiewicz|first=Wes|work=Packers.com|date=March 12, 2018|accessdate=May 26, 2018|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180519153727/http://www.packers.com/news-and-events/article-daily-news-story/article-1/negotiating-window-opens-today-for-pending-nfl-free-agents/d8742ef7-d15c-43be-9959-72d670a9f2b1|archivedate=May 19, 2018}}</ref> He started the season well, with 19 receptions for 289 yards and two touchdowns before suffering a concussion in Week 4.<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.superiortelegram.com/sports/football/4503431-peterson-redskins-stomp-sloppy-packers-31-14 |title=Peterson, Redskins stomp sloppy Packers, 31\u201314 |work=Superior Telegram |access-date=October 9, 2018 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Packers' Geronimo Allison: Enters concussion protocol |url=https://www.cbssports.com/fantasy/football/news/packers-geronimo-allison-enters-concussion-protocol/ |website=CBSSports.com }}</ref> Allison was placed on injured reserve on November 6, 2018 after undergoing groin surgery.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Bouda |first1=Nate |title=Packers Place WR Geronimo Allison on IR, Waive S Jermaine Whitehead |url=http://nfltraderumors.co/packers-place-wr-geronino-allison-on-ir-waive-s-jermaine-whitehead/ |website=NFLTradeRumors.co |accessdate=November 6, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Packers place WR Geronimo Allison on IR, release S Whitehead|url=https://www.packers.com/news/packers-place-wr-geronimo-allison-on-ir-release-s-whitehead|website=Packers.com|date=November 6, 2018}}</ref>\n\n===2019 season===\nOn March 13, 2019, Allison was re-signed by the Packers.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://packerswire.usatoday.com/2019/03/16/packers-officially-keeping-wr-geronimo-allison-on-1-year-deal/|title=Packers officially keeping WR Geronimo Allison on 1-year deal|date=March 15, 2019|work=packerswire.com}}</ref>\n\n==Career NFL statistics==\n===Regular season===\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align: center;\"\n|-\n! rowspan=\"2\"|Year !! rowspan=\"2\"|Team !! colspan=\"2\"|Games !! colspan=\"5\"|Receiving !! 