/span>||bgcolor=\"red\"|<span style=\"color:white;\">Frank</span>||bgcolor=\"red\"|<span style=\"color:white;\">Andre</span>||||||bgcolor=\"red\"|<span style=\"color:white;\">Kelly</span>||bgcolor=\"red\"|<span style=\"color:white;\">Kelly</span>\n|bgcolor=\"#CCCCCC\" colspan=8|\n|-\n!11\n|bgcolor=\"red\"|<span style=\"color:white;\">''Andre''</span>\n|bgcolor=\"red\"|<span style=\"color:white;\">Mike</span>||bgcolor=\"red\"|<span style=\"color:white;\">Bill</span>||bgcolor=\"red\"|<span style=\"color:white;\">Brad</span>||||||bgcolor=\"red\"|<span style=\"color:white;\">Kelly</span>\n|bgcolor=\"#CCCCCC\" colspan=9|\n|-\n!12\n|bgcolor=\"blue\"|<span style=\"color:white;\">''Caleb''</span>\n|||||||bgcolor=\"blue\"|<span style=\"color:white;\">Jim</span>||bgcolor=\"blue\"|<span style=\"color:white;\">Adam</span>\n|bgcolor=\"#CCCCCC\" colspan=10|\n|-\n!13\n|bgcolor=\"blue\"|<span style=\"color:white;\">''Jim''</span>\n|||||||bgcolor=\"blue\"|<span style=\"color:white;\">Iain</span>\n|bgcolor=\"#CCCCCC\" colspan=11|\n|-\n!14\n|bgcolor=\"red\"|<span style=\"color:white;\">''Bill''</span>\n|bgcolor=\"red\"|<span style=\"color:white;\">Kelly</span>||bgcolor=\"red\"|<span style=\"color:white;\">Frank</span>||bgcolor=\"red\"|<span style=\"color:white;\">Kelly</span>\n|bgcolor=\"#CCCCCC\" colspan=12|\n|-\n!15\n|bgcolor=\"red\"|<span style=\"color:white;\">''Frank''</span>\n|bgcolor=\"red\"|<span style=\"color:white;\">Mike</span>||bgcolor=\"red\"|<span style=\"color:white;\">Brad</span>\n|bgcolor=\"#CCCCCC\" colspan=13|\n|-\n!16\n|bgcolor=\"red\"|<span style=\"color:white;\">''Mike''</span>\n|bgcolor=\"red\"|<span style=\"color:white;\">Kelly</span>\n|bgcolor=\"#CCCCCC\" colspan=14|\n|}\n\n==Ratings==\n\n{{Empty section|date=August 2012}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Top Shot}}\n{{History shows}}\n\n[[Category:2010 American television seasons]]\n[[Category:2010s American reality television series]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox television season\n |season_number = 1\n |bgcolour = #5d3954\n |image = <!--  Commented out: [[File:Top-shot.jpg|250px]] -->\n |caption = <!-- no caption needed for images with shows title logo per template instructions -->\n |country = {{USA}}\n |network = [[History (U.S. TV channel)|History]]\n |first_aired = {{Start date|2010|6|6}}\n |last_aired = {{End date|2010|8|15}}\n |num_episodes = 10\n}}\nThe first season of the [[History (U.S. TV channel)|History Channel]] television series '''''[[Top Shot]]''''' commenced airing on June 6, 2010, and concluded on August 15, 2010. The season contained ten episodes, and was filmed over a period of 33 days in the spring in [[Santa Clarita, California]]. The winner of the season was British ex-Army captain [[Iain Harrison]].\n\nIain Harrison later appeared as a coach in Seasons 2, 3, and 4; [[J.J. Racaza]] appeared as a coach in Season 2; [[Kelly Bachand]] appeared as a coach in Season 4; and [[Blake Miguez]] appeared as a coach in Season 2.\n\nChris Cerino, Peter Palma, Kelly Bachand, Adam Benson, and Blake Miguez returned for [[Top Shot (Season 5)|Top Shot: All-Stars]]. Miguez finished in 15th, Bachand finished in 9th, Benson finished in 7th, and Palma finished in 6th, while Cerino was the season's runner-up. According to [[Colby Donaldson]]'s Twitter, J.J Racaza became a father during filming and was unable to come out for the show.\n\n==Contestants==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n! Contestant\n! Occupation / background\n! Original Team\n! Merged Team\n! Eliminated\n|-\n| {{nowrap|'''Mike Seeklander'''}}<br><small>38, [[Owasso, Oklahoma|Owasso, OK]]</small>\n| U.S. Shooting Academy, former [[United States Marine Corps|Marine]], [[Federal Air Marshal Service|Federal Air Marshal]] and firearms instructor\n| bgcolor=\"red\" align=\"center\"|<span style=\"color:white;\">Red Team</span>\n|bgcolor=\"darkgray\"|{{hs|20}}\n|align=\"center\"| 16th Place\n|-\n| '''Frank Campana'''<br><small>47, [[Yonkers, New York|Yonkers, NY]]</small>\n| Retired police officer, [[Federal Bureau o