|Mexico]], Mexico<br />Open<br />|| {{flagicon|ARG}} [[Sanyo Guti\u00e9rrez]] <br> {{flagicon|ARG}} [[Maxi S\u00e1nchez]] || {{flagicon|ESP}} [[Paquito Navarro]] <br> {{flagicon|ESP}} [[Juan Lebr\u00f3n]]\n|}\n\n===December===\n{|class=wikitable style=font-size:85%\n|-\n!width=75|Week of\n!width=230|Tournament\n!width=210|Champions\n!width=210|Runners-up\n|- valign=top\n|12 December|| style=\"background:#ffc;\"| {{flagicon|ESP}} Master Final <br /> [[Barcelona]], Spain<br />WPT Finals<br />|| {{flagicon|ESP}} [[Alejandro Gal\u00e1n]] <br> {{flagicon|BRA}} [[Pablo Lima]] || {{flagicon|ARG}} [[Fernando Belasteguin]] <br> {{flagicon|ARG}} [[Agust\u00edn Tapia]]\n\n{{uncategorized|date=April 2020}}\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Men's Padel pro circuit}}\n\n{{Infobox tennis circuit season\n<!-- Details -->\n| image         =\n| image_caption =\n| image_alt     =\n| image_size    = 100px\n| duration      = 19 March \u2013 15 December\n| edition       = 7th\n| tournaments   = 19\n| categories    = Master Final <br/> Master (5) <br/> Open (10)\n| previous      = [[2018 World Padel Tour|2018]]\n| next          = [[2020 World Padel Tour|2020]]\n<!-- Achievements -->\n| most_tournament_titles = {{flagicon|ESP}} [[Paquito Navarro]] <br> {{flagicon|ESP}} [[Juan Lebr\u00f3n]] <br> {{flagicon|ARG}} [[Sanyo Guti\u00e9rrez]] <br> {{flagicon|ARG}} [[Maxi S\u00e1nchez]] <br> {{flagicon|ESP}} [[Alejandro Gal\u00e1n]] (5)\n| most_tournament_finals = {{flagicon|ESP}} [[Paquito Navarro]]<br/>{{flagicon|ESP}} [[Juan Lebr\u00f3n]]\n| points_leader = {{flagicon|ESP}} [[Paquito Navarro]] <br> {{flagicon|ESP}} [[Juan Lebr\u00f3n]] (10,860)\n}}\n\nThe '''2019 [[World Padel Tour]]''' was the global elite men's professional [[padel tennis]] circuit for the 2019 padel season. The 2019 World Padel Tour calendar was composed of the Masters tournaments, the Masters Finals and the Open tournaments. Most of the tournaments took place in Spain, televised by [[Gol TV]], but there were also tournaments in [[Argentina]], [[Sweden]], [[Brazil]] and [[Mexico]].\n\n==Schedule==\nThis is the complete schedule of events on the 2019 calendar\n\n;Key\n{|class=wikitable style=font-size:95%;width:12%\n|- style=\"background:#ffc;\"\n|WPT Finals\n|- style=\"background:#f0dc82;\"\n|Masters\n|- style=\"background:#e9e9e9;\"\n|Open\n|}\n\n===March===\n{|class=wikitable style=font-size:85%\n|-\n!width=75|Week of\n!width=230|Tournament\n!width=210|Champions\n!width=210|Runners-up\n|- valign=top\n|19 March|| style=\"background:#f0dc82;\"| {{flagicon|ESP}} Marbella Masters <br /> [[Marbella]], Spain<br />Masters<br />|| {{flagicon|ARG}} [[Sanyo Guti\u00e9rrez]] <br> {{flagicon|ARG}} [[Maxi S\u00e1nchez]] || {{flagicon|ESP}} [[Paquito Navarro]] <br> {{flagicon|ESP}} [[Juan Lebr\u00f3n]]\n|}\n\n===April===\n{|class=wikitable style=font-size:85%\n|-\n!width=75|Week of\n!width=230|Tournament\n!width=210|Champions\n!width=210|Runners-up\n|- valign=top\n|9 April|| style=\"background:#e9e9e9;\"| {{flagicon|ESP}} Logro\u00f1o Open <br /> [[Logro\u00f1o]], Spain<br />Open<br />|| {{flagicon|ARG}} [[Sanyo Guti\u00e9rrez]] <br> {{flagicon|ARG}} [[Maxi S\u00e1nchez]] || {{flagicon|ESP}} [[Paquito Navarro]] <br> {{flagicon|ESP}} [[Juan Lebr\u00f3n]]\n|- valign=top\n|23 April|| style=\"background:#e9e9e9;\"| {{flagicon|ESP}} Alicante Open <br /> [[Alicante]], Spain<br />Open<br />|| {{flagicon|ESP}} [[Paquito Navarro]] <br> {{flagicon|ESP}} [[Juan Lebr\u00f3n (padel player)|Juan Lebr\u00f3n]] || {{flagicon|ARG}} [[Fernando Belasteguin]] <br> {{flagicon|BRA}} [[Pablo Lima]]\n|}\n\n===May===\n{|class=wikitable style=font-size:85%\n|-\n!width=75|Week of\n!width=230|Tournament\n!width=210|Champions\n!width=210|Runners-up\n|- valign=top\n|7 May|| style=\"background:#e9e9e9;\"| {{flagicon|ESP}} Vigo Open <br /> [[Vigo]], Spain<br />Open<br />|| {{flagicon|ARG}} [[Sanyo Guti\u00e9rrez]] <br> {{flagicon|ARG}} [[Maxi S\u00e1nchez]] || {{flagicon|ESP}} [[Paquito Navarro]] <br> {{flagicon|ESP}} [[Juan 