ishing second in the league, Wigan qualified for the [[2019 Super League Grand Final|Grand Final]] Play-offs. The warriors won the qualifying final, but lost the in the semi-final and the preliminary final to finish third in the play-off series.\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"font-size:85%;\"\n!Date\n!Match\n!Opponent\n!H/A\n!Result\n!Scorers\n!Att.\n|- style=\"background:#ddffdd\n|20th September 2019\n|Qualifying Final\n|{{leagueicon|Salford city|16}} [[Salford Red Devils]]\n|H\n|18\u201312\n| \n|9,247\n|- style=\"background:#ffdddd\n|27th September 2019\n|Semi-final 1\n|{{leagueicon|st Helens|16}} [[St Helens RFC|St Helens]]\n|[[Totally Wicked Stadium|A]]\n|10\u201340\n| \n|14,508\n|- style=\"background:#ffdddd\n|4th October 2019\n|Preliminary Final\n|{{leagueicon|Salford city|16}} [[Salford Red Devils]]\n|H\n|4\u201328\n| \n|9,858 \n|-\n|}\n\n==Challenge Cup==\n{{main|2019 Challenge Cup}}\nAs a \"Super 8s\" team of the [[Super League XXIII|2018 Super League]], Wigan Warriors entered the [[2019 Challenge Cup]] in the sixth round where they we're subsequently knocked out by [[Warrington Wolves]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/rugby-league/challenge-cup/scores-fixtures/2019-05|title=Coral Challenge Cup - Scores & Fixtures - Rugby League|website=BBC Sport}}</ref>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"font-size:85%;\"\n!Date\n!Round\n!Opponent\n!H/A\n!Result\n!Scorers\n!Att.\n|- style=\"background:#ffdddd\n|12th May 2019\n|Sixth Round\n|{{leagueicon|Warrington|16}} [[Warrington Wolves]]\n|[[Halliwell Jones Stadium|A]]\n|24\u201326\n| \n|7,086\n|-\n|}\n\n==Transfers==\n\n===In===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n!Player\n!From\n!Ref.\n|-\n|[[Joe Bullock (rugby league)|Joe Bullock]]\n|{{leagueicon|Barrow|16}} [[Barrow Raiders]]\n|rowspan=\"3\"|<ref name=\"Transfers\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.totalrl.com/confirmed-super-league-signings-for-2019/|title=Confirmed Super League signings for 2019|first=Matthew|last=Shaw|date=November 15, 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[Zak Hardaker]]\n|Free Agent\n|-\n|[[Jarrod Sammut]]\n|{{leagueicon|London|16}} [[London Broncos]]\n|-\n|}\n\n===Out===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n!Player\n!To\n!Ref.\n|-\n|[[John Bateman (rugby league)|John Bateman]]\n|{{leagueicon|Canberra|16}} [[Canberra Raiders]]\n|rowspan=\"3\"|<ref name=\"Transfers\" />\n|-\n|[[Ryan Sutton]]\n|{{leagueicon|Canberra|16}} [[Canberra Raiders]]\n|-\n|[[Sam Tomkins]]\n|{{leagueicon|Catalans|16}} [[Catalan Dragons]]\n|-\n|}\n\n===Loans Out===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n!Player\n!To\n!Ref.\n|-\n|[[Josh Woods]]\n|{{leagueicon|Leigh|16}} [[Leigh Centurions]]\n|<ref name=\"Transfers\" />\n|-\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{uncategorized|date=April 2020}}\n", "text_old": "{{lead missing|date=February 2020}}\n\n{{Infobox rugby league team season\n | name            = Wigan Warriors 2019 season\n | year            = 2019\n | team_colour     = #DC143C\n | font_colour     = White\n | league          = Super League\n | league_link     = [[Super League XXIV]]\n | league_rank     = 2nd\n | league_wins     = 18\n | league_draws    = 0\n | league_losses   = 11\n | points_for      = 699\n | points_against  = 539\n | playoff_result  = \n | cup             = Challenge Cup \n | cup_result      = 6th Round\n | cup_wins        = 0\n | cup_losses      = 1\n | CEO_title       = Chairman\n | CEO             = [[Ian Lenagan]] \n | coach_title     = Head Coach\n | coach           = [[Adrian Lam]]\n | captain        = [[Sean O'Loughlin]]\n | stadium         = [[DW Stadium]]\n | avg_attendance  = \n | high_attendance = \n | low_attendance  = \n | top_tries       = \n | top_goals       = \n | top_points      = \n | prev_season     = [[2018 Wigan Warriors season|2018]]\n | next_season     = [[2020 Wigan Warriors season|2020]]\n | list            = yes\n | list_link       = List of Wigan Warriors seasons\n| pattern_la1        = _red_hoops\n| pattern_b1         = _whitehoops\n| pattern_ra1        = _red_hoops\n| pattern_sh1        = \n| pattern_so1        = _hoops_re